> Stir-fries are an unbeatable weeknight dinner – simple, fast, and delicious. This
> beef is marinated with intensely aromatic ingredients for incredible results. If
> you have time, let it marinate in the fridge for up to an hour to marry the flavors!

Bring a #medium pot{} of water with a large pinch of @salt{} to a boil. Mince or
grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Thinly slice the
@scallions{2}, keeping the whites and greens separate. Trim and discard the bottom
inch of the @baby broccoli{6%ounce}. Halve the broccolini lengthwise through the
stems, then cut into 2-inch pieces.

Cook the rice: Add the @brown rice{3/4%cup} to the boiling water and cook for
~{30-35%minutes}, until tender. Drain.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @soy sauce{6%tsp}, @hoisin sauce{1%tbsp},
scallion whites, half the garlic, and half the ginger. Add the @ground beef{12%ounce}
and thoroughly mix with your hands.

With 15-20 minutes left on the rice, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a
#large pan{} over medium heat. Add the broccolini and cook, tossing, for
~{6-8%minutes}, until crisp-tender. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the
remaining garlic and ginger and cook, tossing for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.
Remove from the pan and set aside. Cover to keep warm.

Heat the same #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the beef and cook,
breaking up the meat into pieces, until browned and no longer pink.

Finish and plate: Fluff the rice with a #fork{}. Serve the broccolini and beef on a
bed of rice, sprinkled with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Enjoy!